<typeStatus box="[354,458,1627,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[468,489,1627,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="84" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(Code 07-MYCOPA, 
<figureCitation box="[749,881,1627,1654]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 23–30" captionStart-1="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId-0="7.[151,264,1824,1848]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox-0="[154,1436,1000,1796]" captionTargetBox-1="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId-0="figure-422@7.[150,1437,993,1801]" captionTargetId-1="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURES 23–30. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. 23, Habitus (lateral view); 24, head (frontolateral view); 25, head and thorax, (lateral view); 26, ditto (dorsal view); 27, abdomen (dorsal view); 28, ditto (lateral view); 29–30, wing (red arrows indicating costal breaks).Abbreviations: or1, orbital seta 1; or3, orbital seta 3; i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta; vb, vibrissa; p dc s, posterior dorsocentral seta; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; ktp s, katepisternal seta; TII, tergite 2; TIII, tergite 3; TIV, tergite 4; TV, tergite 5; TVI; tergite 6." captionText-1="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566059" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5566059/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Figs 23–36</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[903,967,1627,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[984,1115,1627,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,1000,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-422@7.[150,1437,993,1801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. 23, Habitus (lateral view); 24, head (frontolateral view); 25, head and thorax, (lateral view); 26, ditto (dorsal view); 27, abdomen (dorsal view); 28, ditto (lateral view); 29–30, wing (red arrows indicating costal breaks).Abbreviations: or1, orbital seta 1; or3, orbital seta 3; i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta; vb, vibrissa; p dc s, posterior dorsocentral seta; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; ktp s, katepisternal seta; TII, tergite 2; TIII, tergite 3; TIV, tergite 4; TV, tergite 5; TVI; tergite 6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566059/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Figs 23–26</figureCitation>
). Dark brown; eyes reddish and glabrous; facial carina light brown, prominent; scape and pedicel light brown; flagellomere 1 brown; arista with four dorsal and one ventral branches, and terminal fork; orbital plates dark brown, lighter after orbital bristle 3 (or3); orbital setae dark brown; distance between or1 and or2 = 
<quantity box="[900,1003,1735,1761]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="0.03">0.03 mm</quantity>
, between or1 and or3 = 
<quantity box="[1280,1383,1735,1761]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="0.06">0.06 mm</quantity>
, and between or2 and or3 = 
<quantity box="[408,510,1771,1797]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="0.03">0.03 mm</quantity>
; frons light brown, reflecting silvery shine throughout; ocellar triangle dark brown, approximately 1/3 as long as the frons; occiput light brown; face light brown; gena light (with silvery brilliance similar to that on frons); proboscis and labellum light; palps light brown; postocellar setae dark brown, long and crossed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[251,340,1879,1905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[356,572,1878,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,1000,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-422@7.[150,1437,993,1801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. 23, Habitus (lateral view); 24, head (frontolateral view); 25, head and thorax, (lateral view); 26, ditto (dorsal view); 27, abdomen (dorsal view); 28, ditto (lateral view); 29–30, wing (red arrows indicating costal breaks).Abbreviations: or1, orbital seta 1; or3, orbital seta 3; i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta; vb, vibrissa; p dc s, posterior dorsocentral seta; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; ktp s, katepisternal seta; TII, tergite 2; TIII, tergite 3; TIV, tergite 4; TV, tergite 5; TVI; tergite 6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566059/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Figs 23, 25 and 26</figureCitation>
). Dark brown; scutum shiny dark brown, with 8 regular rows of acrostichal setulae; pleura pale yellow, with a dark brown region in the dorsal portion of the proepisternum, anepisternum and anepimeron forming a confluent band with the notum coloration above the wing insertion; a pair of posterior dorsocentral setae; scutellum opaque with converging basal and distal scutellar setae; legs uniformly pale yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[244,465,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,1000,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-422@7.[150,1437,993,1801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. 23, Habitus (lateral view); 24, head (frontolateral view); 25, head and thorax, (lateral view); 26, ditto (dorsal view); 27, abdomen (dorsal view); 28, ditto (lateral view); 29–30, wing (red arrows indicating costal breaks).Abbreviations: or1, orbital seta 1; or3, orbital seta 3; i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta; vb, vibrissa; p dc s, posterior dorsocentral seta; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; ktp s, katepisternal seta; TII, tergite 2; TIII, tergite 3; TIV, tergite 4; TV, tergite 5; TVI; tergite 6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566059/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 23, 29 and 30</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, stained in the second C break and extending to the vein M; costal lappet dilated and dark; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[420,445,205,219]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">2+3</subScript>
straight towards C; veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[757,783,205,219]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">4+5</subScript>
and M slightly converging near the apex of the wing; bmcu absent; halter light on the connecting stem, knob damaged; index: C = 1.22, ac = 4.35, hb = 0.60, 4c = 1.90, 4v = 2.65, 5x = 2.6, M = 0.81, prox. x = 0.59. Length 
<quantity box="[719,821,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.60 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[903,1006,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.199999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="0.72">0.72 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1017,1134,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1148,1358,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,1000,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-422@7.[150,1437,993,1801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. 23, Habitus (lateral view); 24, head (frontolateral view); 25, head and thorax, (lateral view); 26, ditto (dorsal view); 27, abdomen (dorsal view); 28, ditto (lateral view); 29–30, wing (red arrows indicating costal breaks).Abbreviations: or1, orbital seta 1; or3, orbital seta 3; i vt s, inner vertical seta; o vt s, outer vertical seta; vb, vibrissa; p dc s, posterior dorsocentral seta; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; ktp s, katepisternal seta; TII, tergite 2; TIII, tergite 3; TIV, tergite 4; TV, tergite 5; TVI; tergite 6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566059/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 23, 27 and 28</figureCitation>
). Dark brown; TI light; TII dark brown, with slight dorsal median indentation and light trapezoidal spot on lateral portion; TIII–V dark brown with a thin light marginal spot; TIV and V with a light, right-angled triangular spot on the side, TV with a pair of dorsal shine light spots; TVI light and shine; sternites and intersegmental membranes light. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Body length:</emphasis>
<quantity box="[242,345,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.09" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="2.09">2.09 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,390,438,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Male terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[404,531,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 31–36</figureCitation>
). Epandrium with equal width and length, microtricose, with 4 upper and 4 lateral setae (Epan, 
<figureCitation box="[299,474,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 31 and 32</figureCitation>
); ventral lobe slightly longer than the surstylus, tapering apically, microtrichose and with 5 long setae (V.L.Epan, 
<figureCitation box="[482,655,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 31 and 32</figureCitation>
). Cerci free (not fused to epandrium), microtrichose, with large setae (Cer, 
<figureCitation box="[215,388,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 31 and 32</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite wide, connected to the surstyli (S.S., 
<figureCitation box="[1076,1157,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Surstylus connected to epandrium, with 10 prensisetae arranged in line, 2 inner and 4–5 outer setae (Sur, 
<figureCitation box="[1059,1226,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 31 and 32</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium arcshaped, as wide as long, being almost the same length as the epandrium (Hypan, 
<figureCitation box="[1059,1229,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 33 and 36</figureCitation>
). Pregonites large, sub-rectangular, partially fused to the hypandrium and bearing a seta (Preg, 
<figureCitation box="[1020,1239,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 33, 34 and 36</figureCitation>
). Phallus tubular, projected anteriorly, with basiphallus 2x narrower than distiphallus (sense 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D. A." box="[1006,1176,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" pagination="103 - 268" refId="ref9032" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. (1987) Phylogenetics and taxonomy of Zygothrica (Diptera: Drosophilidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 186, 103 - 268." type="journal article" year="1987">Grimaldi 1987</bibRefCitation>
), the narrowed section about 1/3 of the phallus length in lateral view; the apical region forked and indented, with rows of tiny setulae on the inner margin (Phallus, 
<figureCitation box="[450,579,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 33–35</figureCitation>
). Phallapodeme laterally flattened and shorter than phallus (Phallap, 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 34 and 35</figureCitation>
). Ventral rod (sense 
<bibRefCitation author="Bachli, G. &amp; Vilela, C. R. &amp; Escher, S. A. &amp; Saura, A." box="[454,652,799,825]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 362" refId="ref8625" refString="Bachli, G., Vilela, C. R., Escher, S. A., Saura, A. (2004) The Drosophilidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 39, 1 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047414681" type="journal article" year="2004">
Bächli 
<emphasis box="[533,589,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
) anteriorly projected and merged with the posteromedial margin of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[302,476,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 33 and 36</figureCitation>
). Postgonites (connected to the pregonites) elongated and curved anteriorly in lateral view, bearing approximately three apical setulae, and microtrichose on the inner surface (Post and Preg, 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,950,974]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,181,926]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[153,1433,181,926]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Holotype (♂07-MYCOPA) of Mycodrosophila martinsae n. sp. Male terminalia: 31, epandrium, surstyli and cerci (posterior view); 32, ditto (postero-lateral view); 33, phallus, hypandrium, pregonites and postgonites (ventral view); 34, pregonite, postgonite, ventral rod, phallus and phallapodeme (lateral view); 35, phallus, ventral rod and phallapodeme (lateral view); 36, pregonites, postgonites, hypandrium and ventral rod insertion scar (ventral view). Abbreviations: Cer, cerci; Epan, epandrium; Sur, surstylus; V.L.Epan, ventral lobe of epandrium; S.S, subepandrial sclerite; Hypan, hypandrium; Preg, pregonite; Post, postgonite; V.R., ventral rod; Phallap, phallapodeme; V.R.I.S., ventral rod insertion scar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566061/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs 33, 34 and 36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,969]" box="[199,408,943,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Female: unknown.</paragraph>
